headline: Raphaël Varane: 'Showing vulnerability does not mean you're weak'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the retired footballer shares his experiences with mental health issues during his career and calls on his sport to break the silence around these problems, which affect an estimated 20% to 35% of professional players.

headline: When private anger turns into a social force
description: In France, anger is everywhere: in the public sphere, in the media and at the ballot box. The majority of French people under the age of 35 say they have experienced it. From private feelings to collective outcries, they search for ways to channel this emotion.

headline: Gay Talese, the last titan of the American press
description: He was a pioneer of New Journalism, a movement that transformed American journalism with a literary writing style. At 93, the author of the landmark 1966 profile 'Frank Sinatra Has a Cold,' finds his daily life increasingly constrained by old age.
